Questions:

Should the script include optional prompts for user confirmation before actions like driver installation or system restarts?

1.9s
"Should the script include optional prompts for user confirmation before actions like driver installation or system restarts?"
no prompts at all. it must be zero interaction. if a restart is needed, it will be commented (#) out and echo a message that a restart is required.

"Are there preferred error-handling outputs, such as logging to a file or emailing results?"
Whatever helps you troubleshoot.

"Does the script need to support multi-GPU setups explicitly, or assume single GPU?"
Assume single local GPU, for now. There may be peers on the network in the future which also may have a GPU which we can monitor from the master console.

"Should it check for and handle existing NVIDIA drivers before autoinstall?"
yes. the nvidia drivers will always be installed prior to using this script.
months or years down the road all the version numbers could be different or higher.

bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y cockpit pcp cockpit-pcp pcp-pmda-nvidia-gpu

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
apt update -y
ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."

reboot
else
echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp cockpit-pcp

Install NVIDIA PMDA
if [ -d /var/lib/pcp/pmdas/nvidia ]; then
cd /var/lib/pcp/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | ./Install
else
echo "NVIDIA PMDA directory not found. Check PCP installation."
exit 1
fi

Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

Setup Cockpit extension (basic)
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
"version": 1,
"tools": {
"gpu-monitor": {
"label": "GPU Monitor",
"path": "index.html"
}
},
"content-security-policy": "default-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://cdn.jsdelivr.net; form-action 'self'; connect-src 'self' ws: wss:"
}
EOF

Create index.html
cat > index.html << EOF

GPU Monitor    
GPU Monitor
GPU Utilization Graph

GPU Temperature Graph

All NVIDIA Metrics
Metric	Value
 EOF
Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp gettext nodejs npm make git

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
if [ -d /var/lib/pcp/pmdas/nvidia ]; then
  cd /var/lib/pcp/pmdas/nvidia
  echo "daemon" | ./Install
else
  echo "NVIDIA PMDA directory not found. Check PCP installation."
  exit 1
fi

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
rm -rf /tmp/gpu-monitor /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
git clone https://github.com/cockpit-project/starter-kit.git /tmp/gpu-monitor
cd /tmp/gpu-monitor
npm install @patternfly/react-charts
npm install
make dist
cp -r dist /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Override with custom files if needed, but use starter-kit as base for React
# Assume starter-kit has basic setup; customize as per guide

# For custom code, replace index.jsx with the guide's code
cat > /tmp/gpu-monitor/src/index.jsx << EOF
import cockpit from 'cockpit';
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import ReactDOM from 'react-dom';
import { Card, CardTitle, CardBody, Grid, GridItem, Table, TableHeader, TableBody, TableVariant, sortable } from '@patternfly/react-core';
import { Chart, ChartAxis, ChartGroup, ChartLine, ChartThemeColor, ChartVoronoiContainer } from '@patternfly/react-charts';

const GPUMonitor = () => {
  const [metrics, setMetrics] = useState({});
  const [utilHistory, setUtilHistory] = useState([]);
  const [tempHistory, setTempHistory] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    const interval = setInterval(() => {
      cockpit.spawn(["pmrep", "-s", "1", "-t", "1s", "nvidia"])
        .then(output => {
          const lines = output.split('\\n');
          const newMetrics = {};
          lines.forEach(line => {
            const parts = line.split(/\\s+/);
            if (parts.length > 1) {
              newMetrics[parts[0]] = parts[1];
            }
          });
          setMetrics(newMetrics);

          const now = new Date();
          setUtilHistory(prev => [...prev, { x: now, y: parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.gpuactive'] || 0) }].slice(-60));
          setTempHistory(prev => [...prev, { x: now, y: parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.temperature'] || 0) }].slice(-60));
        })
        .catch(error => console.error('Error fetching metrics:', error));
    }, 5000);

    return () => clearInterval(interval);
  }, []);

  const metricList = Object.entries(metrics).map(([key, value]) => ({ key, value }));

  const columns = [
    { title: 'Metric', transforms: [sortable] },
    { title: 'Value', transforms: [sortable] }
  ];

  return (
    
      
        
          GPU Utilization Graph
          
             \`\${datum.y}%\`} />}
              domain={{ y: [0, 100] }}
              height={250}
              padding={{ bottom: 50, left: 50, right: 50, top: 50 }}
              themeColor={ChartThemeColor.blue}
              width={450}
            >
               t.toLocaleTimeString()} />
              
                
              
            
          
        
      
      
        
          GPU Temperature Graph
          
             \`\${datum.y}C\`} />}
              domain={{ y: [0, 100] }}
              height={250}
              padding={{ bottom: 50, left: 50, right: 50, top: 50 }}
              themeColor={ChartThemeColor.blue}
              width={450}
            >
               t.toLocaleTimeString()} />
              
                
              
            
          
        
      
      
        
          All NVIDIA Metrics
          
             [row.key, row.value])}>
              
              
            

          
        
      
    
  );
};

document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
  ReactDOM.render(, document.getElementById('app'));
});
EOF

# Rebuild after override
make dist
cp -r dist /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Update index.html with correct paths
cat > /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor/index.html << EOF



  
  GPU Monitor
  
  


  

  


EOF

Thought for 213s
bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp gettext nodejs make git nvidia-cuda-toolkit

# Install build dependencies for PCP
apt install -y bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses5-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/releases/download/pcp-6.2.0/pcp-6.2.0.src.tar.gz
tar xzf pcp-6.2.0.src.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.2.0
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var --lib64=no
make -C src/pmdas/nvidia
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
rm -rf /tmp/gpu-monitor /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
git clone https://github.com/cockpit-project/starter-kit.git /tmp/gpu-monitor
cd /tmp/gpu-monitor
npm install @patternfly/react-charts @patternfly/react-core
npm install
make dist
cp -r dist /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Override with custom files
cat > /tmp/gpu-monitor/src/index.jsx << EOF
import cockpit from 'cockpit';
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import ReactDOM from 'react-dom';
import { Card, CardTitle, CardBody, Grid, GridItem, Table, Tbody, Tr, Td, Thead, Th } from '@patternfly/react-core';
import { Chart, ChartAxis, ChartGroup, ChartLine, ChartThemeColor, ChartVoronoiContainer } from '@patternfly/react-charts';

const GPUMonitor = () => {
  const [metrics, setMetrics] = useState({});
  const [utilHistory, setUtilHistory] = useState([]);
  const [tempHistory, setTempHistory] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    const interval = setInterval(() => {
      cockpit.spawn(["pmrep", "-s", "1", "-t", "1s", "nvidia"])
        .then(output => {
          const lines = output.split('\\n');
          const newMetrics = {};
          lines.forEach(line => {
            const parts = line.trim().split(/\\s+/);
            if (parts.length >= 2) {
              newMetrics[parts[0]] = parts[1];
            }
          });
          setMetrics(newMetrics);

          const now = new Date();
          setUtilHistory(prev => [...prev, { x: now, y: parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.gpuactive'] || 0) }].slice(-60));
          setTempHistory(prev => [...prev, { x: now, y: parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.temperature'] || 0) }].slice(-60));
        })
        .catch(error => console.error('Error fetching metrics:', error));
    }, 5000);

    return () => clearInterval(interval);
  }, []);

  return (
    
      
        
          GPU Utilization Graph
          
             \`\${datum.y}%\`} />}
              domain={{ y: [0, 100] }}
              height={250}
              padding={{ bottom: 50, left: 50, right: 50, top: 50 }}
              themeColor={ChartThemeColor.blue}
              width={450}
            >
               new Date(t).toLocaleTimeString()} />
              
                
              
            
          
        
      
      
        
          GPU Temperature Graph
          
             \`\${datum.y}C\`} />}
              domain={{ y: [0, 100] }}
              height={250}
              padding={{ bottom: 50, left: 50, right: 50, top: 50 }}
              themeColor={ChartThemeColor.blue}
              width={450}
            >
               new Date(t).toLocaleTimeString()} />
              
                
              
            
          
        
      
      
        
          All NVIDIA Metrics
          
            
                {Object.entries(metrics).map(([key, value]) => (
                  
                ))}
              

              
                

                  Metric
                  Value
                

              
              

                    {key}
                    {value}
                  

            

          
        
      
    
  );
};

ReactDOM.render(, document.getElementById('app'));
EOF

# Rebuild
make dist
cp -r dist /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Update index.html
cat > /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor/index.html << EOF



  
  GPU Monitor
  
  


  

  


EOF

# Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses5-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/releases/download/v6.2.0/pcp-6.2.0.src.tar.gz
tar xzf pcp-6.2.0.src.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.2.0
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var --lib64=no
make -C src/pmdas/nvidia
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
  "version": 1,
  "tools": {
    "gpu-monitor": {
      "label": "GPU Monitor",
      "path": "index.html"
    }
  }
}
EOF

# Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << EOF



  GPU Monitor
  
  
  
  


  
GPU Monitor

  

    
GPU Utilization Graph

    
  

  

    
GPU Temperature Graph

    
  

  

    
All NVIDIA Metrics

    

      
MetricValue

      
    

  

  


EOF

# Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

md@nn06:~$ cat cp.sh
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses5-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/releases/download/v6.2.0/pcp-6.2.0.src.tar.gz
tar xzf pcp-6.2.0.src.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.2.0
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var --lib64=no
make -C src/pmdas/nvidia
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
  "version": 1,
  "tools": {
    "gpu-monitor": {
      "label": "GPU Monitor",
      "path": "index.html"
    }
  }
}
EOF

# Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << EOF



  GPU Monitor
  
  
  
  


  
GPU Monitor

  

    
GPU Utilization Graph

    
  

  

    
GPU Temperature Graph

    
  

  

    
All NVIDIA Metrics

    

      
MetricValue

      
    

  

  


EOF

# Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var --lib64=no
make -C src/pmdas/nvidia
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
  "version": 1,
  "tools": {
    "gpu-monitor": {
      "label": "GPU Monitor",
      "path": "index.html"
    }
  }
}
EOF

# Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << EOF



  GPU Monitor
  
  
  
  


  
GPU Monitor

  

    
GPU Utilization Graph

    
  

  

    
GPU Temperature Graph

    
  

  

    
All NVIDIA Metrics

    

      
MetricValue

      
    

  

  


EOF

# Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
apt update -y
ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."

reboot
else
echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
make -C src/pmdas/nvidia
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
"version": 1,
"tools": {
"gpu-monitor": {
"label": "GPU Monitor",
"path": "index.html"
}
}
}
EOF

Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << EOF

GPU Monitor    
GPU Monitor
GPU Utilization Graph

GPU Temperature Graph

All NVIDIA Metrics
Metric	Value


EOF
Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
apt update -y
ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."

reboot
else
echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
make
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
"version": 1,
"tools": {
"gpu-monitor": {
"label": "GPU Monitor",
"path": "index.html"
}
}
}
EOF

Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << EOF

GPU Monitor    
GPU Monitor
GPU Utilization Graph

GPU Temperature Graph

All NVIDIA Metrics
Metric	Value


EOF
Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
apt update -y
ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."

reboot
else
echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
make
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep -f nvidia-persistenced; then
nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << EOF
{
"version": 1,
"tools": {
"gpu-monitor": {
"label": "GPU Monitor",
"path": "index.html"
}
}
}
EOF

Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << EOF

GPU Monitor    
GPU Monitor
GPU Utilization Graph

GPU Temperature Graph

All NVIDIA Metrics
Metric	Value


EOF
Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

IP=$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}')
echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://${IP}:9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

10.3s

#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
apt update -y
ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."

reboot
else
echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev

Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
make
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << 'EOF'
{
"version": 1,
"tools": {
"gpu-monitor": {
"label": "GPU Monitor",
"path": "index.html"
}
}
}
EOF

Create index.html with CDN and correct cockpit.js
cat > index.html << 'EOF'

GPU Monitor    
GPU Monitor
GPU Utilization Graph

GPU Temperature Graph

All NVIDIA Metrics
Metric	Value


EOF
Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

IP=$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}')
echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://${IP}:9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

sed -e 's;^include .*pcp.conf;include $(PCP_DIR)/etc/pcp.conf;' \
    -e 's;^BUILDRULES.*=.*buildrules;BUILDRULES = $\(PCP_INC_DIR\)/buildrules;' \
    -e 's;^INSTALL_SH.*=.*install-sh;INSTALL_SH = $\(PCP_BINADM_DIR\)/install-sh;' \
    -e 's;^GENPMDA.*=.*genpmda;GENPMDA = $\(PCP_BIN_DIR\)/genpmda;' \
    -e 's;-I\$(TOPDIR)/src/include/pcp;-I$(PCP_INC_DIR);' \
    -e 's;-I\$(TOPDIR)/src/include;-I$(PCP_INC_DIR)/..;' \
    -e '/^PCPLIB_LDFLAGS/s;-L.*;-L$(PCP_LIB_DIR);' \
    -e '/^[     ][      ]*-L\$(TOPDIR)/d' \
        < builddefs > builddefs.install

=== libpcp_static ===
for d in `echo src `; do if test -d "$d" -a -f "$d/GNUmakefile"; then /usr/bin/echo === $d ===; make --no-print-directory -C $d default || exit $?; fi; done

Thought for 323s
The script executed successfully, but the GPU Monitor page in Cockpit is blank with console errors due to:

Incorrect path for cockpit.js (MIME type 'text/html' indicates 404 response).
CSP blocks external CDN (chart.js) and inline script/style.
To fix, update the script as follows (replaces index.html creation, adds local chart.js download):

bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev wget

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
make
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Download chart.js locally (CSP blocks CDN)
wget https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js -O chart.js

# Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << 'EOF'
{
  "version": 1,
  "tools": {
    "gpu-monitor": {
      "label": "GPU Monitor",
      "path": "index.html"
    }
  }
}
EOF

# Create index.html (no inline style/script for CSP)
cat > index.html << 'EOF'



  GPU Monitor
  
  
  
  
  


  
GPU Monitor

  

    
GPU Utilization Graph

    
  

  

    
GPU Temperature Graph

    
  

  

    
All NVIDIA Metrics

    

      
MetricValue

      
    

  



EOF

# Create gpu-monitor.css
cat > gpu-monitor.css << 'EOF'
body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 20px; }
.chart-container { width: 80%; margin: 20px auto; }
table { width: 80%; margin: 20px auto; border-collapse: collapse; }
th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
th { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
EOF

# Create gpu-monitor.js
cat > gpu-monitor.js << 'EOF'
const utilChartCtx = document.getElementById('utilizationChart').getContext('2d');
const tempChartCtx = document.getElementById('temperatureChart').getContext('2d');
const utilChart = new Chart(utilChartCtx, { type: 'line', data: { labels: [], datasets: [{ label: 'Utilization', data: [] }] }, options: { scales: { y: { min: 0, max: 100 } } } });
const tempChart = new Chart(tempChartCtx, { type: 'line', data: { labels: [], datasets: [{ label: 'Temperature', data: [] }] }, options: { scales: { y: { min: 0, max: 100 } } } });
const metricsBody = document.getElementById('metricsBody');

function updateCharts() {
  cockpit.spawn(["pmrep", "-s", "1", "-t", "1s", "nvidia"])
    .then(output => {
      const lines = output.split('\\n').filter(line => line.trim());
      const newMetrics = {};
      lines.forEach(line => {
        const parts = line.trim().split(/\\s+/);
        if (parts.length >= 2) {
          newMetrics[parts[0]] = parts[1];
        }
      });

      const now = new Date().toLocaleTimeString();
      utilChart.data.labels.push(now);
      utilChart.data.datasets[0].data.push(parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.gpuactive'] || 0));
      if (utilChart.data.labels.length > 60) utilChart.data.labels.shift();
      if (utilChart.data.datasets[0].data.length > 60) utilChart.data.datasets[0].data.shift();
      utilChart.update();

      tempChart.data.labels.push(now);
      tempChart.data.datasets[0].data.push(parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.temperature'] || 0));
      if (tempChart.data.labels.length > 60) tempChart.data.labels.shift();
      if (tempChart.data.datasets[0].data.length > 60) tempChart.data.datasets[0].data.shift();
      tempChart.update();

      metricsBody.innerHTML = '';
      for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(newMetrics)) {
        const row = document.createElement('tr');
        row.innerHTML = `${key}${value}`;
        metricsBody.appendChild(row);
      }
    })
    .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
}

setInterval(updateCharts, 5000);
updateCharts();
EOF

# Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

IP=$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}')
echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://${IP}:9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."

=== libpcp_static ===
for d in `echo src `; do if test -d "$d" -a -f "$d/GNUmakefile"; then /usr/bin/echo === $d ===; make --no-print-directory -C $d default || exit $?; fi; done

bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

LOG_FILE="/var/log/gpu-cockpit-setup.log"

exec > >(tee -a "$LOG_FILE") 2>&1

echo "Starting Cockpit with PCP for NVIDIA GPU monitoring setup on Ubuntu 24.04 Server - $(date)"

# Enable universe repository
add-apt-repository universe -y

# Assume NVIDIA drivers are installed; check nvidia-smi
if ! command -v nvidia-smi &> /dev/null; then
  echo "NVIDIA drivers not found. Installing recommended drivers."
  apt update -y
  ubuntu-drivers autoinstall
  echo "Drivers installed. Reboot required."
  # reboot
else
  echo "NVIDIA drivers detected."
fi

# Get driver major version
DRIVER_VERSION=$(nvidia-smi --query-gpu=driver_version --format=csv,noheader | cut -d. -f1)

# Install libnvidia-cfg1 if missing
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"; then
  echo "Installing libnvidia-cfg1-$DRIVER_VERSION"
  apt install -y libnvidia-cfg1-"$DRIVER_VERSION"
fi

# Update and install packages
apt update -y
apt install -y --no-install-recommends cockpit -t noble-backports
apt install -y --no-install-recommends pcp nvidia-cuda-toolkit bison flex g++ libavahi-common-dev libavahi-client-dev libavahi-glib-dev libmicrohttpd-dev libncurses-dev libreadline-dev libsasl2-dev python3 python3-dev python3-setuptools libpcp3-dev libpcp-pmda3-dev wget

# Install NVIDIA PMDA
wget https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/archive/refs/tags/6.3.7.tar.gz
tar xzf 6.3.7.tar.gz
cd pcp-6.3.7
./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
make
cd src/pmdas/nvidia
echo "daemon" | sudo ./Install

# Enable and start services
systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket pmcd pmlogger

# Kill existing persistenced if running
pkill -f nvidia-persistenced || true

# Enable persistence mode
nvidia-smi -pm 1

# Start persistenced daemon
if ! pgrep nvidia-persistenced; then
  nvidia-persistenced --persistence-mode
fi

# Restart PCP services
systemctl restart pmcd pmlogger

# Verify metrics
if pmprobe -v nvidia.gpuactive; then
  echo "NVIDIA GPU metrics available."
else
  echo "Error: NVIDIA GPU metrics not available. Check logs."
fi

# Setup Cockpit extension
mkdir -p /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor
cd /usr/share/cockpit/gpu-monitor

# Download chart.js locally
wget https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js -O chart.js

# Create manifest.json
cat > manifest.json << 'EOF'
{
  "version": 1,
  "tools": {
    "gpu-monitor": {
      "label": "GPU Monitor",
      "path": "index.html"
    }
  }
}
EOF

# Create index.html
cat > index.html << 'EOF'



  GPU Monitor
  
  
  
  
  


  
GPU Monitor

  

    
GPU Utilization

    
  

  

    
GPU Temperature

    
  

  

    
All NVIDIA Metrics

    

      
MetricValue

      
    

  



EOF

# Create gpu-monitor.css
cat > gpu-monitor.css << 'EOF'
body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 20px; }
.gauge-container { width: 200px; margin: 20px auto; text-align: center; }
table { width: 80%; margin: 20px auto; border-collapse: collapse; }
th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
th { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
EOF

# Create gpu-monitor.js
cat > gpu-monitor.js << 'EOF'
const utilGaugeCtx = document.getElementById('utilizationGauge').getContext('2d');
const tempGaugeCtx = document.getElementById('temperatureGauge').getContext('2d');

const utilGauge = new Chart(utilGaugeCtx, {
  type: 'doughnut',
  data: {
    datasets: [{
      data: [0, 100],
      backgroundColor: ['green', 'lightgray'],
      borderWidth: 0
    }]
  },
  options: {
    circumference: 180,
    rotation: 270,
    cutout: '60%',
    plugins: {
      legend: { display: false },
      tooltip: { enabled: false }
    }
  }
});

const tempGauge = new Chart(tempGaugeCtx, {
  type: 'doughnut',
  data: {
    datasets: [{
      data: [0, 100],
      backgroundColor: ['blue', 'lightgray'],
      borderWidth: 0
    }]
  },
  options: {
    circumference: 180,
    rotation: 270,
    cutout: '60%',
    plugins: {
      legend: { display: false },
      tooltip: { enabled: false }
    }
  }
});

const metricsBody = document.getElementById('metricsBody');

function updateMetrics() {
  cockpit.spawn(["pminfo", "-f", "nvidia"])
    .then(output => {
      const lines = output.split('\n');
      const newMetrics = {};
      let currentMetric = '';
      lines.forEach(line => {
        line = line.trim();
        if (line && !line.startsWith('inst')) {
          currentMetric = line;
        } else if (line.startsWith('inst') && currentMetric) {
          const valueMatch = line.match(/value ([\d.]+)/);
          if (valueMatch) {
            newMetrics[currentMetric] = valueMatch[1];
          }
        }
      });

      // Update gauges
      const utilValue = parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.gpuactive'] || 0);
      utilGauge.data.datasets[0].data = [utilValue, 100 - utilValue];
      utilGauge.data.datasets[0].backgroundColor = [utilValue > 80 ? 'red' : 'green', 'lightgray'];
      utilGauge.update();

      const tempValue = parseFloat(newMetrics['nvidia.temperature'] || 0);
      tempGauge.data.datasets[0].data = [tempValue, 100 - tempValue];
      tempGauge.data.datasets[0].backgroundColor = [tempValue > 80 ? 'red' : tempValue > 60 ? 'orange' : 'green', 'lightgray'];
      tempGauge.update();

      // Update table
      metricsBody.innerHTML = '';
      for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(newMetrics)) {
        const row = document.createElement('tr');
        row.innerHTML = `${key}${value}`;
        metricsBody.appendChild(row);
      }
    })
    .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
}

setInterval(updateMetrics, 5000);
updateMetrics();
EOF

# Restart Cockpit
systemctl restart cockpit.socket

IP=$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}')
echo "Setup complete. Access Cockpit at http://${IP}:9090"
echo "If charts are blank, verify data collection and plugin configuration."
